<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ871027-0036 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief:Data Architects Inc.</HL><DD> 10/27/87</DD><SO>  </SO><IN> DAI MITSYCOMPUTERS (EDP) </IN><TEXT>   Data Architects Inc., Waltham, Mass., said it signed an agreement with Mitsui Comtek, a subsidiary of Mitsui andamp; Co., to market Data Architects' software products, including its electronic funds transfer system, in Japan.    Under the agreement, Data Architects said, it will receive a 50% to 60% share of the profit resulting from sales.    Data Architects said Mitsui, which will initially concentrate on marketing the transfer system, is the first authorized distributor of the product in Japan. Data Architects makes computer software for the banking, insurance and telecommunications industries. </TEXT></DOC>